{{Notability|date=September 2016}}
'''''Blame The Monkey''''' is an American blog focusing on [[travel photography]] inspiration and education, particularly regarding an [[image editing]] technique used in photographic [[Image editing|post processing]] that it calls "Advanced Dynamic Blending."

The site was voted "Best New Blog for Photographers" by [[Scott Kelby]] in his roundup of 55 best of things in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=My “Best of 2011” Awards|url=http://scottkelby.com/my-best-of-2011-awards/|author = [[Scott Kelby]]|accessdate=29 August 2016}}</ref> The blog's author [[Elia Locardi]] was voted ninth in [[USA Today]] 10Best’s "Top Travel Photography Bloggers" in a 2014 Readers' Choice Poll.<ref>{{cite web|title=Top Travel Photography Bloggers Exposed in New Readers' Choice Poll|url=http://www.10best.com/awards/new-media-awards/best-travel-photography-bloggers|publisher=USA Today Travel Media Group|website=10Best|accessdate=29 August 2016}}</ref>

Founded in 2010 by Elia Locardi and Naomi Locardi, the blog shares stories of the photographers’ experiences being [[global nomad]]s living on the road and the techniques used in the creation of the travel photography images. The blog also shares photography tutorials.

