{{notability|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Experiential Education | cover = Journal_of_Experiential_Education.gif | editors = Jayson Seaman | discipline = [[Experiential education]] | former_names = | abbreviation = J. Exp. Educ. | publisher = [[Sage Publications]] on behalf of the [[Association for Experiential Education]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1978-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal202222/title | link1 = http://jee.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://jee.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 1053-8259 | eISSN = 2169-009X | OCLC = 817971290 | LCCN = 82646064 }}
The '''''Journal of Experiential Education''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering the field of [[experiential education]]. The journal's [[editor-in-chief]] is Jayson Seaman ([[University of New Hampshire]]). It was established in 1978 and is published by [[Sage Publications]] on behalf of the [[Association for Experiential Education]].
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in [[Educational Resources Information Center|ERIC]] and [[EBSCO Publishing|EBSCO databases]].
